---
import NoteBox from "@components/NoteBox.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHeroVisual from "@components/PageHeroVisual.astro";
import LabNoteFooter from "@components/LabNoteFooter.astro";
import { PERSON, SITE } from "@data/site";

const title = "From Process Signals to Inspection Evidence in LMD";
const description =
  "A practical chain for connecting Laser Metal Deposition monitoring signals, AI anomaly flags, inspection findings, and final quality evidence.";
const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  headline: title,
  description,
  author: { "@id": `${SITE.canonicalUrl}/identity#manish-sharma`, name: PERSON.name },
  datePublished: SITE.lastUpdated,
  dateModified: SITE.lastUpdated,
  url: `${SITE.canonicalUrl}/lab-notes/from-process-signals-to-inspection-evidence-in-lmd`
};
---

<Layout title={`${title} — Manish Sharma Lab`} description={description} canonical="/lab-notes/from-process-signals-to-inspection-evidence-in-lmd" jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <article class="site-shell py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(22rem,0.52fr)] lg:items-center">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="metric-label">Lab note · 2026-05-09</p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 text-5xl font-black leading-tight text-white md:text-6xl">{title}</h1>
      </div>
      <PageHeroVisual variant="evidence" class="hidden lg:block" />
    </div>
    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1.25fr]">
      <div class="grid h-fit gap-4">
        <NoteBox title="Short answer">
          Process signals become useful when they are linked to inspection evidence and measured outcomes.
        </NoteBox>
        <NoteBox title="Common mistake" tone="laser">
          Treating a monitoring alert as the defect itself, instead of a signal that should route attention toward validation.
        </NoteBox>
        <NoteBox title="Practical takeaway" tone="steel">
          Build a chain: signal, anomaly, suspected risk, inspection method, acceptance criterion, expert decision.
        </NoteBox>
      </div>
      <div class="prose-lab">
        <p>
          In LMD, process signals can include images, videos, pyrometry, machine logs, parameter histories, operator notes, and geometry measurements. AI can help organize these signals and detect unusual patterns.
        </p>
        <p>
          The useful question is not whether a signal looks unusual. The useful question is what physical risk the signal may represent and which inspection method can confirm or reject that risk.
        </p>
        <p>
          A practical workflow links monitoring signals to suspected failure modes, then links those failure modes to dimensional inspection, NDT, metallography, hardness, mechanical testing, or functional testing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <LabNoteFooter links={[
        { label: "LMD Failure Atlas", href: "/frameworks/lmd-failure-atlas" },
        { label: "LMD Quality Evidence Ladder", href: "/frameworks/lmd-quality-evidence-ladder" },
        { label: "Melt-pool monitoring glossary", href: "/glossary/melt-pool-monitoring" }
      ]} />
  </article>
</Layout>
